get.description:
Returns the connection mode of every backend the app talks to. Each value is either `live` (real backend reachable) or `memory` (in-process fallback). Use this to spot misconfigured infrastructure without reading logs.

**Example response**:
```
{
  "service": "docket",
  "status": "ok",
  "backends": {
    "storage": "live", "metadata": "live",
    "records": "live", "events": "live", "cache": "live"
  },
  "time": "2026-07-02T20:00:00Z"
}
```
